The SAM7K PISTOL
Arsenal, Inc., the premier American importer and manufacturer of Kalashnikov-pattern rifles and pistols, is proud to offer to the American enthusiast the Bulgarian-made SAM7K Pistol. This 7.62x39mm caliber pistol combines authentic, high-quality features rarely seen in the American market. Every component of the SAM7K is engineered to provide decades of dependable service. The SAM7K pistol is bound to become a sought-after shooter and collectible firearm.

Arsenal’s Exclusive Milled And Forged Receiver
Each SAM7K receiver is milled from a hot-die hammer forged receiver blank by the Arsenal Co. of Bulgaria. Other milled-receiver AKs are machined from bar stock, but Arsenal’s hot-die hammer forging produces stronger and finer-grained steel. Internal voids and cooling deformations are eliminated by the 5-ton hammer forging process.

Each forged receiver blank requires over 5.5 hours of milling before assembly. This forging and milling process is complex and time-intensive, but Arsenal’s meticulous attention to detail delivers a receiver of unequalled strength, precision and durability

Summary: SAM7K - 7.62x39mm caliber Pistol, milled receiver (hot-die hammer forged), short gas system, front sight block / gas block combination, 10 1/2 inch chrome lined hammer forged barrel, black polymer furniture, original pistol grip made to work with ambidextrous safety lever, and peep rear sight, scope rail. FEATURES

postcontent:
This M1 Carbine was built by the Standard Products during World War II. 

Standard Products produced 247,155 M1 Carbines between April 1943 and July 1944. Serial numbers in Standard Products' production run range from 1,982,520 to 2,352,519, and this M1 Carbine has a serial number of 2143XXX. It has an Underwood barrel stamped 12-43. 

- 1st style of barrel band without bayonet lug
- Straight face on slide
- Early magazine catch
- push safety
- Flip-up rear sight (first version)

All early features and original finishes on this M1 Carbine make is very collectible. 

I can take and send you pictures of specific parts/marks if you are interested.

title: For Sale:  M1 Carbine .30 Carbine Rifle by Quality Hardware from WWII/Korea
postcontent:
This M1 Carbine was built by the Quality Hardware during World War II. 

Quality Hardware produced 359,666 M1 Carbines between December 1942 and April 1944. Serial numbers in Quality Hardware's last production run range from 4,632,100 to 4,879,525, and this M1 Carbine has a serial number of 4824XXX. It has an Underwood barrel from 1944. The barrel has an Arlington Ordnance stamp on the bottom of the barrel in compliance with the 1968 Gun Control Act, requiring Lend/Lease and Military Assistance Program guns being imported back to the US to have the importer's stamp. In this case, the rifle returned home from Korea. 

- 3rd style of barrel band with bayonet lug
- Angled face on slide
- Later magazine catch with support arm for higher capacity magazines
- rotary safety
- Milled adjustable rear sight

I can take and send you pictures of specific parts/marks if you are interested. It's a great M1 Carbine if you are looking for a shooter or an affordable addition to your collection.
